fields.name: Cheekwood Estate & Gardens
fields.details: Once the family home of Mabel and Leslie Cheek, this extraordinary 1930s estate, with its historic mansion and 55 acres of cultivated gardens and expansive vistas, today serves the public as a botanic garden, arboretum and museum.

fields.name: Ryman Auditorium
fields.details: Ryman Auditorium is a historic 2,362-seat live-performance venue located at 116 Rep. John Lewis Way North, in Downtown Nashville, Tennessee. Tours available throughout the daytime hours. Special event timing varies based on event

fields.name: Ascend Amphitheater
fields.details: The Ascend Amphitheater is an open-air event venue located on the Cumberland River in Nashville, Tennessee. It is set inside the Metro Riverfront Park. The amphitheater seats 2,300 in fixed seating, and 4,500 on the lawn, with a total capacity of 6,800

fields.name: Brooklyn Bowl
fields.details: Welcome to Brooklyn Bowl Nashville! Catch a rockin' show, strike down some pins, grab a bite, and sip and chill on our patio. We've got a little something for everyone. Voted Pollstar 2022's Best New Concert Venue! Eat. Drink. Rock. And Roll.

fields.name: FirstBank Amphitheater
fields.details: FirstBank Amphitheater, a world-class boutique amphitheater nestled within a beautiful, wooded, natural stone and park-like setting. Located at the Graystone Quarry in Thompsonâ€™s Station at the southern border of Franklin, Tennessee, FirstBank Amphitheater opened in 2021 bring back memorable music experiences for fans and artists.

fields.name: Geodis Park
fields.details: Geodis Park, formerly known as Nashville SC Stadium and Nashville Fairgrounds Stadium, is a 30,000-seat soccer-specific stadium at the historic Nashville Fairgrounds in Nashville, Tennessee. It is the home of Major League Soccer club Nashville SC.

fields.name: City Winery
fields.details: A unique culinary & cultural experience for urban wine enthusiasts passionate about music. We create unforgettable private events. Weddings, corporate events, celebrations & more.

fields.name: Bridgestone Arena
fields.details: Bridgestone Arena is a multi-purpose venue in downtown Nashville, Tennessee, United States. Completed in 1996, it is the home of the Nashville Predators of the National Hockey League.

fields.name: The Frist
fields.hours: Mon, Fri, Sat 10AM-5:30PM; Thur 10AM-8PM; Sun 1PM-5:30PM; Tues & Wed(CLOSED)
fields.details: The Frist Art Museum, formerly known as the Frist Center for the Visual Arts, is an art exhibition hall in Nashville, Tennessee, housed in the city's historic U.S. Post Office building, which is listed on the National Register of Historic Places.

fields.name: Nashville Municipal Auditorium
fields.details: The Nashville Municipal Auditorium is an indoor sports and concert venue in Nashville, Tennessee. It opened October 7, 1962 with both an arena and exhibition hall. The former exhibition hall has been permanent home to the Musicians Hall of Fame and Museum since 2013

fields.name: TPAC
fields.details: The Tennessee Performing Arts Center, or TPAC, is located in the James K. Polk Cultural Center at 505 Deaderick Street in downtown Nashville, Tennessee. It occupies a city block between 5th and 6th Avenues North and Deaderick and Union Streets

fields.name: Nissan Stadium
fields.details: Nissan Stadium is a multi-purpose stadium in Nashville, Tennessee, United States. Owned by the Metropolitan Government of Nashville and Davidson County, it is primarily used for football and is the home field of the Tennessee Titans of the National Football League and the Tigers of Tennessee State University.

fields.name: Marathon Music Works
fields.details: With a standing room capacity of 1,500 and over 14,000 sq. ft., Marathon can entertain parties of up to 600 in formal banquet seating, 750 in a theater arrangement, and 900 in cocktail functions. The versatile, open floor design is accented with exposed brick walls, a lofty steel beam ceiling, polished concrete bars, and metal chandeliers your guests will love.
